props.synopsis: AFL grand final day has arrived, with Collingwood and Brisbane ready to do battle at the MCG with a premiership on the line. Follow live.

title.children: Son of a gun stars in curtain-raiser as Pies and Lions prepare for AFL grand final

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Not many surprises on Thursday night when the teams were named, as both clubs were fairly open with their thought process during the week. Dan McStay was ruled out early and Billy Frampton was confirmed as his replacement for Collingwood. The only surprise was the elevation of Jack Ginnivan into the starting 22 in place of Pat Lipinski, who will be the Magpies' sub. Brisbane meanwhile opted against risking Jack Payne, sticking with Darcy Gardiner in back line. The Lions will confirm their sub later, but it will almost certainly be Jarryd Lyons. Final teams will be confirmed at 1:30pm.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: The grand final teams

children.content: Not many surprises on Thursday night when the teams were named, as both clubs were fairly open with their thought process during the week.

Dan McStay was ruled out early and Billy Frampton was confirmed as his replacement for Collingwood. The only surprise was the elevation of Jack Ginnivan into the starting 22 in place of Pat Lipinski, who will be the Magpies' sub.
Brisbane meanwhile opted against risking Jack Payne, sticking with Darcy Gardiner in back line. The Lions will confirm their sub later, but it will almost certainly be Jarryd Lyons.
Final teams will be confirmed at 1:30pm.
